<div class="balanced-diet-section">
	<div class="balanced-diet diet text-center">
		<h4>A BALANCED DIET</h4>
		<p>Fat is essential to human wellbeing, it provides energy and makes you feel full. Our bodies require both saturated and unsaturated fats in order to absorb vitamins A, D, E and K.  We make sure to include both fats in your meals: saturated fat, mostly found in animal foods and unsaturated, mostly found in plant foods. The amount of fat in your diet will be calculated and reflected in your food boxes. 
		<br></br> 
		Most of your meals will contain complex carbohydrates. These do an excellent job of keeping you full and are less fattening because they take longer for our bodies to metabolise them. Most of the carbohydrates in our menus derive from plenty of seeds, green and root vegetables, pseudocereals and grains. Using this knowledge we create meals which aid your body in regulating its blood sugar levels. 
		<br></br>
		Protein is integral to our daily menus as they are the building blocks of life. We need protein in our diet to help repair cells and regenerate new ones. We all require a certain amount of protein to maintain good health, whether in the form or animal or plant protein. Animal proteins include meats, fish and eggs, whilst plant sources include soy, beans, legumes, nut butters and pseudocereals.
		</p>
	</div>
