			<h6>GRAINS, PSEUDOCEREALS, NUTS, SEEDS AND LEGUMES</h6>
			<p>The only grains we use in our meals are black, brown and red rice. Other than that we focus on pseudocereals; buckwheat, amaranth and quinoa. These are free from gluten and rich in amino acids.  You wi ll see nuts and seed scattered all over our menus and we like to use legumes as a source of added protein.
			<br></br> 
			All grains, pseudocereals, nuts, seeds and legumes have a natural, protective layer called phytic acid – an anti nutrient that irritates the gut. Although a small amount of phytic acid is healthy, we activate these ingredients by soaking them. This starts the germination process and reduces the amount of phytic acid, which makes their nutrients easier to absorb and digest by your body. 
			</p>
